he strong presence of the surname in 16th-century Cornwall and Devon is unexpected, but is probably the result of migration from counties further east or north. Derivation from the Cornish language is implausible, and there is no known place in Cornwall which could have given rise to it as a habitational name."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."],"variants":[{"name":"Anni","meanings":["Pet form of   Ann   or   Anne ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Anne Gersende de Conty was born in 1252, in Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, her father, Ghislain de Conty, was 32 and her mother, Louise De Domart, was 23. She married Gilles D' Amiens on 14 February 1272, in Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in 1296, in Amiens, Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 44."},"et":{"1252–1296":"1252–1296","1250–1284":"1250–1284","1278–1323":"1278–1323","1220–1258":"1220–1258","1229–1275":"1229–1275","1258":"1258","1323":"1323","1278":"1278","1275":"1275","1220":"1220","1252":"1252","14 February 1272":"14. veebruar 1272","1296":"1296","1284":"1284","1250":"1250","1229":"1229","Conty, Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Amiens, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1252–1296":"1252–1296","1250–1284":"1250–1284","1278–1323":"1278–1323","1220–1258":"1220–1258","1229–1275":"1229–1275","1258":"1258","1323":"1323","1278":"1278","1275":"1275","1220":"1220","1252":"1252","14 February 1272":"14. helmikuuta 1272","1296":"1296","1284":"1284","1250":"1250","1229":"1229","Conty, Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Amiens, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska","Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Conty, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Ranska